  "decision_conditions": [
    "The development permitted shall be begun before the expiration of three years from the date of this permission.",
    "Reason: In order to comply with the provisions of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990 (as amended).",
    "| The development hereby approved shall be carried out in accordance with drawing title number(s) PL/PP/2696-00, Block & Location Plans, received 28 June 2016; PL/PP/2696-01, Existing Ground Floor Plan, received 28 June 2016;  PL/PP/2696-02, Existing First and Second Floor Plan, received 28 June 2016; PL/PP/2696-03, Existing Elevations, received 28 June 2016; PL/PP/2696-04 rev A, Proposed Ground Floor Plan, received 1 August 2016; PL/PP/2696-05 rev A, Proposed First and Second Floor Plan, received 14 September 2016; PL/PP/2696-06 rev A, Proposed Elevations, received 14 September 2016; PL/PP/2696-06 rev A, Proposed Elevations (section), received 14 September 2016.",
    "Reason: For the avoidance of doubt, in the interest of proper planning.",
    "| Notwithstanding the details shown on the plans, all external materials to be used in the development shall match the appearance of those of the existing building.",
    "Reason: To ensure that the materials harmonise with the surroundings, in accordance with policies 1.1 & 1.2 of the Ealing Core Strategy (2012), policies 7.4 & 7B of the Ealing Development Management Development Plan Document (2013), policies 7.4 & 7.6 of the London Plan (2016) and the National Planning Policy Framework (2012).",
    "| Notwithstanding the provisions of Article 3 of the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) (England) Order 2016 (as amended) (or any subsequent amendment or new Order), no windows or other openings (other than those shown on the submitted plans) shall be formed in the walls or roof of the building permitted.",
    "Reason:  To protect residential amenity, in accordance with policies 1.1 & 1.2 of the Ealing Core Strategy (2012), policies 7.4 & 7B of the Ealing Development Management Development Plan Document (2013), policies 7.4 & 7.6 of the London Plan (2016), and the National Planning Policy Framework (2012).",
    "| Ensure refuse and recycling storage (bins) and a refuse and recycling enclosure are provided and brought into use prior to the first occupation of the development permitted and retained thereafter.",
    "Reason:  To protect the living conditions of occupiers of the area and in the interests of the future occupants of the development in accordance with policies with policies 3.5 and 7B of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013), and policy 5.16 of the London Plan (2016).",
    "| A minimum of three cycle parking spaces shall be provided and located in a secure undercover lockable compound, prior to the first occupation of the development permitted and retained thereafter.",
    "Reason:  In the interests of highway and pedestrian safety in accordance with policies 1.1 f of the Ealing Core Strategy (2012), policy 6.9 of the London Plan (2016), and the National Planning Policy Framework (2012)."
  ],
